						<summary>

						<p>Pillar set up in the small rock-cut cave close to the cave.</p>						

						<p>PRATĀPARUDRA.</p>						

						<p>1293 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1214, Māgha, ba. 11. Monday, corresponding to February 2, Tuesday 1293 A.D. <hi rend="italic">f.d.t.</hi> 61.</p>						

						<p>Unfinished and refers probably to a gift to the god Anantaśayana at Uṇḍavelli for the merit of the king Pratāparudra.</p>						

						</summary>
